gomodel:SYNGO_3063  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Analysis of dendritic spines after ProSAPiP1 overexpression and knockdown in mature primary hippocampal neurons\"\n- \"We found that overall spine number (Figure (Figure4A,4A, left panel) and the percentage of filopodia (Figure (Figure4A,4A, right panel) were reduced after ProSAPiP1 overexpression.\"\n- \"The effects on spine density and morphology after ProSAPiP1 knockdown were not as strong; we only found a slight, but significant decrease in the number of mushroom-like spines (Figure (Figure4B,4B, right panel).\"\n- \"Taken together, these data implicate that a postsynaptic ProSAPiP1/SPAR module promotes the maturation of dendritic spines.\". Experimental description: - \"Primary hippocampal neurons were prepared from rat embryos at E18/E19...\"\n- Overexpressed Lzts3; Prosapip1 is of rat species (traced back to PMID:16522626): \" Cloning of a Full-length Rat ProSAPiP1 cDNA\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3063" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

